{"questionId":"9066452","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Physical properties of elements vary according to atomic number. Sections 6 to 9 of the data<br>booklet list some of these properties.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Melting points and boiling points of elements 1 to 95</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7e051c51fe7dbc81de0824cb07025b4c6bcc350d.png\" width=\"698\" height=\"443\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Sketch how the first ionization energies of elements vary with their atomic radius.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/962b393f9ac7a5fcf250333cf7b1d204207d50fa.png\" width=\"351\" height=\"327\"></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/d25a30b8517cb5c424f3db00b1786eeee111ddfc.png\" width=\"297\" height=\"281\"> &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔]</span></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Note:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Accept any negative sloping line.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Do <strong>not</strong> award mark if line touches either axis.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066452","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ1.1b(iv)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Sketch how the first ionization energies of elements vary with their atomic radius.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(iv)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Periodicity","3.2 Periodic trends","Core","Topic 3: Periodicity"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}